<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Helpful experience with Windows 10 Pro (after high CPU l]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7506&amp;p=32718#p32718"><![CDATA[
For the removed text size options, I recommend you to check out the freeware, Winaero Tweaker. Be careful with tweaking the sizes though. Better make a backup of your Registry by creating a System Restore point first.<br /><br />Depending on the system DPI, the window metrics registry settings sometimes have no effect. You must tweak them after your system DPI setting is final and then export the registry key at HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Control Panel\Desktop\WindowMetrics to backup them.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Sat May 20, 2017 12:40 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
